\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Group 1:
 Farmers residing in two districts (Kabarole and Hoima) where WFP was not actively procuring maize through large buyers.
 Farmers in these two districts were randomly selected in two stages:
 first villages 50 villages were selected from a list of all villages,
 with sampling probabilities proportional to the number of households living in the village.
 Next,
 in each village 10 households were randomly selected from the list obtained from the village headquarters.
 This group will also be referred to as the control group.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Group 2:
 Farmers who live in districts with characteristics similar to those in Group 1,
 but where maize is procured from farmers under the indirect conditional contract modality.
 Specifically,
